Implemented a focused slice of the refactor in the app path.

**Changed**
- `[ToolPartView.tsx](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/ToolPartView.tsx)` now renders `v3.ToolPart` directly in both transcript and detail contexts. It no longer adapts through `ToolCall`, and it handles permission approvals and question answers from the `ToolPart` state itself.
- `[toolPartMeta.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/toolPartMeta.ts)` adds v3-native helpers for titles, subtitles, status, permission state, and question state.
- `[message/[messageId].tsx](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/app/(app)/session/[id]/message/[messageId].tsx)` now uses the v3 tool part directly for the header, status indicator, and full view.
- `[sync.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/sync.ts)` no longer contains the app-side direct `/v3/sessions/:id/messages` HTTP fetch/send path. Message fetch/send now goes through `AppSyncStore` / `SyncNode`, and the dead outbox/seq/background-send code was removed.
- Deleted the active converter path: `[toolPartToToolCall.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/toolPartToToolCall.ts)` and its old test, replaced by `[toolPartMeta.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/components/parts/toolPartMeta.test.ts)`.

**Verified**
- `yarn workspace happy-app typecheck`
- `yarn workspace happy-app test --run sources/components/parts/toolPartMeta.test.ts`
- I also confirmed the branch’s `@slopus/happy-sync` package was already green here: unit tests, typecheck, and `sync-node.integration.test.ts` all passed before these app changes.

**Remaining Gaps**
- The full spec is still not complete. Legacy runtime pieces still exist in the repo, especially `[apiSession.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/api/apiSession.ts)` and its callers in Codex/Gemini/OpenClaw/offline paths.
- Flattened legacy app tool/message types still exist under `[typesMessage.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/typesMessage.ts)` and older tool components still reference them.
- `SyncSocket` / `apiSocket` still exists for other app paths at `[apiSocket.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-app/sources/sync/apiSocket.ts)`.

If you want, I can continue on the next slice and remove the CLI-side `ApiSessionClient` fallback path.
